@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - identity/User
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Load desired User spec and status from\nKubernetes;
:Resolve OCI state via GetUser with ListUsers\nfallback;
:Use oci_identity_users filters compartment_id,\nexternal_identifier, identity_provider_id,\nname (+1 more) when OCID lookup or\nbind-versus-create needs list resolution;
if (Resource exists?) then (yes)
:Update path calls UpdateUser;
:Guard mutable fields defined_tags,\ndescription, email, freeform_tags and\nforce-new fields compartment_id, name;
else (no)
:Create path calls CreateUser;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource;
:Apply repo-authored secret policy none;
:Delete path uses DeleteUser with required via\nGetUser or ListUsers to DELETED confirmation;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: identity
slug: user
kind: User
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update none;
delete DELETING
mutable/forceNew: defined_tags, description,
email, freeform_tags / compartment_id, name
open gaps: none
The generated runtime reads back the OCI user
after create or update and projects the response
into status.
Finalizer removal waits for delete confirmation
through Get or list fallback.
No secret side effects or legacy adapter seams
are involved in the current User path.
end note
@enduml
